This paper discusses the phenomenon of double descent in deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of model size and training epochs on performance, which are relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of model complexity, which is relevant to the subfield of statistics (cs.ST).
